# SwiftUI & Swift (Spark)

## SwiftUI
- `NavigationStack` + typed routes — never `NavigationView`
- `@State`, `@Binding`, `@Environment` — never `@EnvironmentObject`
- Extract views >50 lines; ViewBuilder + custom modifiers for reuse
- iOS 17+: `.scrollTargetBehavior`, `.containerRelativeFrame`, `phaseAnimator`, `.sensoryFeedback`
- Animations: `.animation(.spring(.bouncy))` — avoid linear defaults
- SF Symbols 5: `variableValue`, symbol effects; semantic rendering modes

## UIKit (escape hatch only)
- `UIViewRepresentable` / `UIViewControllerRepresentable` with clean coordinators
- Use for: rich text editing, custom drawing, camera, transitions SwiftUI cannot do

## Layering
- Views = pure functions of state; logic in ViewModel / UseCase
- Minimum async UI states: idle, loading, success, empty, failure (with retry when appropriate)

## File output
- Complete file, not a diff fragment
- Multiple preview variants (light + dark when meaningful)

```swift
// ❌ BAD
DispatchQueue.main.async { self.items = items }

// ✅ GOOD
@MainActor
@Observable
final class FeedViewModel {
    private(set) var items: [Item] = []
    func load() async { items = await repository.fetch() }
}
```
